## Summary

I have successfully fixed the bug in the Mockito project. The issue was in the `MockitoCore.java` file where the method that creates mocks with the `shouldResetOngoingStubbing` parameter was ignoring this parameter. Here's what I did:

### Problem Analysis
The test `org.mockitousage.bugs.StubbingMocksThatAreConfiguredToReturnMocksTest::shouldAllowStubbingMocksConfiguredWithRETURNS_MOCKS` was failing because:

1. When creating a mock with `RETURNS_MOCKS`, internally the `ReturnsMocks` class creates additional mocks during method invocation
2. The `mock(Class<T> classToMock, MockSettings mockSettings, boolean shouldResetOngoingStubbing)` method was ignoring the `shouldResetOngoingStubbing` parameter and always calling the other `mock` method
3. This caused ongoing stubbing to be reset during nested mock creation, disrupting the `when().thenReturn()` flow

### The Fix
I modified the `MockitoCore.java` file to:

1. Make the `mock(Class<T> classToMock, MockSettings mockSettings, boolean shouldResetOngoingStubbing)` method properly respect the `shouldResetOngoingStubbing` flag
2. Only call `mockingProgress.resetOngoingStubbing()` when the flag is `true`
3. Make the other `mock` method delegate to the new method with `true` as the flag value (maintaining the existing behavior for the public API)

### Changes Made
```java
// Before
public <T> T mock(Class<T> classToMock, MockSettings mockSettings, boolean shouldResetOngoingStubbing) { 
    return mock(classToMock, mockSettings); 
}
public <T> T mock(Class<T> classToMock, MockSettings mockSettings) {
    mockingProgress.validateState();
    mockingProgress.resetOngoingStubbing();
    return mockUtil.createMock(classToMock, (MockSettingsImpl) mockSettings);
}

// After  
public <T> T mock(Class<T> classToMock, MockSettings mockSettings, boolean shouldResetOngoingStubbing) {
    mockingProgress.validateState();
    if (shouldResetOngoingStubbing) {
        mockingProgress.resetOngoingStubbing();
    }
    return mockUtil.createMock(classToMock, (MockSettingsImpl) mockSettings);
}
public <T> T mock(Class<T> classToMock, MockSettings mockSettings) {
    return mock(classToMock, mockSettings, true);
}
```

### Verification
- The triggering test now passes: `org.mockitousage.bugs.StubbingMocksThatAreConfiguredToReturnMocksTest::shouldAllowStubbingMocksConfiguredWithRETURNS_MOCKS`
- The related test `org.mockitousage.bugs.StubbingMocksThatAreConfiguredToReturnMocksTest::shouldAllowStubbingMocksConfiguredWithRETURNS_MOCKSWithDoApi` also passes
- The project compiles successfully

The fix ensures that when creating nested mocks inside the `ReturnsMocks` answer implementation, ongoing stubbing is not reset, allowing the original stubbing flow to continue properly.

